FBIS4-63895 "drsov102_g_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-102 Daily Report 25 May 1994 WESTERN REGION Belarus Statement on Civil Defense Exercise, Radiation Levels Statement on Civil Defense Exercise, Radiation Levels LD2505164994 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1200 GMT 25 May 94 LD2505164994 Minsk Radio Minsk Network Belarusian BFN [Text] Official report: On 24 May, according to the Minsk Oblast civil defense procedures plan, planned quarterly training was held for the networks of supervision and laboratory monitoring. Elaborate radiation protection measures were put into operation in Myadelskiy Rayon, Minsk Oblast. According to evidence obtained from the Main Hydrometeorology Service, the State Atomic Supervision and the leadership of the Ignalina nuclear power station, at 1200 today the radiation situation around the Ignalina nuclear power station was within normal limits. Since April, one generating unit at the station itself has been undergoing a scheduled overhaul. The second generating unit has been halted for economic reasons and is not producing electricity.
